cs.CV, cs.IM, cs.MM, cs.MS, cs.NA 

The paper discusses image processing and analysis techniques for fibre-bundle endomicroscopy, which involves the acquisition of high-resolution images of internal organs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), image processing (cs.IM), multimedia (cs.MM), medical imaging (cs.MS), or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Among these, cs.CV and cs.IM are the most likely, as they specifically deal with image analysis and processing. cs.MM is also likely, as it deals with multimedia data, which includes images. cs.MS is relevant due to the medical imaging aspect of the paper, while cs.NA is relevant due to the numerical methods used in image processing.
